ZH: 我们的经济状况迫使我们削减开支。
EN: Our economic situation forces us to cut spending.

ZH: 她的疾病迫使她放弃了原本的计划。
EN: Her illness compelled her to give up her original plan.

ZH: 这场危机迫使我重新考虑我的未来。
EN: This crisis compelled me to reconsider my future.

ZH: 高昂的物价迫使人们调整消费习惯。
EN: High prices force people to adjust their consumption habits.

ZH: 内外压力迫使政府采取行动。
EN: Pressures from within and outside force the government to take action.

ZH: 这个项目的时间紧迫，迫使我们加班加点。
EN: The tight deadline of this project forces us to work overtime.

ZH: 部队面临着敌人的迫使，迅速做出了反应。
EN: Faced with the pressure from the enemy, the troops reacted swiftly.

ZH: 紧急情况下，迫使我们做出了艰难的决定。
EN: In an emergency, we were compelled to make a difficult decision.

ZH: 这次考试的挑战迫使我努力学习。
EN: The challenge of this exam compels me to study hard.

ZH: 贫困迫使他们寻求更好的生活出路。
EN: Poverty forces them to seek a better way of life.

ZH: 他对自己的梦想充满了迫使。
EN: He is full of drive towards his dreams.

ZH: 战争迫使他离开了家乡。
EN: The war compelled him to leave his hometown.

ZH: 生计的压力迫使他接受了一份不喜欢的工作。
EN: The pressure of making a living compelled him to take a job he didn't like.

ZH: 她的坏习惯迫使她做出了一系列错误的决定。
EN: Her bad habits led her to make a series of wrong decisions.

ZH: 这种艰难的环境迫使他们发挥出最大的潜力。
EN: The challenging environment forces them to unleash their full potential.

ZH: 经济危机迫使公司进行裁员。
EN: The economic crisis compels the company to lay off employees.

ZH: 他对失败的恐惧迫使他变得更加努力。
EN: His fear of failure drives him to work harder.

ZH: 这个目标的重要性迫使我们付出更大的努力。
EN: The importance of this goal compels us to put in more effort.

ZH: 快要迟到了，迫使我加快了脚步。
EN: Running late forced me to walk faster.

ZH: 时间的紧迫迫使我们加快工作进度。
EN: The urgency of time forces us to speed up our work progress.
